<p style="line-height:normal;background:white"><b><u><span style="font-size:20.0pt;color:#222222">About Rupin Pass Trek </span></u></b></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;color:#222222">&nbsp;</span></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;color:#222222">Rupin Pass has been used by local shepherds
and pastoralist communities, especially Bhotiya and Kinnauri tribes, for
seasonal migrations (moving livestock grazing, etc.). </span></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;color:#222222">It
also served as a trade route between southern Uttarakhand and the Sangla region
of Kinnaur. </span></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;color:#222222">The
route was also used by small pilgrim or local travel movements; though concrete
records about early pilgrim use are scarcer.</span></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;color:#222222">&nbsp;</span></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;color:#222222">The
Rupin Pass Trek is an adventurous journey that takes you through some of the
most beautiful and remote parts of the Indian Himalayas. It’s important to plan
and prepare adequately before embarking on this trek to ensure a safe and
enjoyable experience.</span></p>






<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;color:#222222"><br /></span></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;color:#222222">The&nbsp;<b>Rupin
Pass Trek</b>&nbsp;stands out among many Himalayan treks for several unique
reasons that make it a popular choice for trekkers. Here’s why you might choose
Rupin Pass Trekking :</span></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;
color:#222222">&nbsp;</span></b></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;
color:#222222">Stunning Waterfalls and River Crossings</span></b></p>






<ul><li>The trek is famous for its <span style="font-weight: bold;">waterfalls </span>, especially the <span style="font-weight: bold;">three-stage Rupin waterfall</span>, which is a rare sight in the Himalayas. You get to walk alongside the Rupin River and cross it multiple times, making water a constant and refreshing companion throughout the journey.</li><li>&nbsp;</li></ul>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;
color:#222222">Dramatic Landscape Changes of rupin valley</span></b></p>




<ul><li><span style="text-indent: -18pt; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: 12pt;">One of the most captivating aspects of Rupin Pass is the&nbsp;</span><b style="text-indent: -18pt; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: 12pt;">dramatic
variation in landscapes.&nbsp;</b>Trekkers begin in the lush green forests of
Uttarakhand, pass through quaint villages, traverse flowery meadows, and end up
in the stark, barren high-altitude terrain near the pass. Each day brings
something completely new.</li></ul>




<p><br /></p>






<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;
color:#222222">The Hanging Village of Jhaka/ Sewa&nbsp; Village</span></b></p>






<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: 12pt; text-indent: -18pt;">The&nbsp;</span><b style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: 12pt; text-indent: -18pt;">hanging village of Jhaka</b><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: 12pt; text-indent: -18pt;">&nbsp;is a highlight for
many trekkers. Its precarious location on a cliff makes it look like it’s
suspended in the air, providing a unique cultural experience and incredible
views.</span></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;color:#222222">&nbsp;</span></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;
color:#222222">Adventure and Thrill</span></b></p>








<ul type="discd">
	<li style="color:#222222;text-align:justify;
	line-height:normal;
	background:white"><span style="font-size:12.0pt">The&nbsp;<b>snow
	bridges</b>, high-altitude pass crossing, and challenging terrain make the
	trek ideal for adventurers. The journey to the pass itself is thrilling,
	especially the climb through snowfields and boulder sections. If you enjoy
	the challenge of high-altitude trekking, Rupin Pass delivers in spades. <b>Panoramic
	Views from Rupin Pass</b></span></li>
</ul>








<ul type="discd">
	<li style="color:#222222;text-align:justify;
	line-height:normal;
	background:white"><span style="font-size:12.0pt">At an altitude
	of&nbsp;<b>15,250 feet</b>, the summit of Rupin Pass offers&nbsp;<b>panoramic
	views of the Kinner Kailash range</b>, and several other Himalayan peaks
	in Himachal Pradesh. The sense of accomplishment upon reaching the pass,
	coupled with these breathtaking views, is deeply rewarding.</span></li>
</ul>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;color:#222222">&nbsp;</span></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;
color:#222222">Himachal and Kinnur Cultural Experience</span></b></p>






<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: 12pt; text-indent: -18pt;">The trek takes you through remote villages like Jiskun Sewa and
Jhaka, giving you a glimpse into the lives of the local mountain communities.
You’ll experience warm hospitality, taste local food, and gain insights into
their way of life, which remains largely untouched by modernity.</span></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;
color:#222222">&nbsp;</span></b></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;
color:#222222">Less Crowded Trekking Route</span></b></p>






<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: 12pt; text-indent: -18pt;">While the Rupin Pass is gaining popularity, it is still&nbsp;</span><b style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: 12pt; text-indent: -18pt;">less
crowded</b><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: 12pt; text-indent: -18pt;">&nbsp;compared to treks like Others trekking route , making it a
more peaceful and serene experience. If you’re looking for solitude and a
deeper connection with nature, Rupin Pass is an excellent choice.</span></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;
color:#222222">&nbsp;</span></b></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;
color:#222222">Photogenic of Rupin Pass Trek</span></b></p>






<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: 12pt; text-indent: -18pt;">The variety in landscapes—from hanging villages to waterfalls,
expansive meadows, snow-covered passes, and panoramic mountain views—makes
Rupin Pass Trek a&nbsp;</span><b style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: 12pt; text-indent: -18pt;">photographer’s dream</b><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-size: 12pt; text-indent: -18pt;">. Every turn of the trail
offers a new opportunity for breathtaking photos.</span></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;
color:#222222">&nbsp;</span></b></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;
color:#222222">The Big Achievement</span></b></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;
color:#222222">Crossing a Rupin Pass high-altitude Trek</span></b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;color:#222222">: Rupin is a personal achievement.
The physical challenge, combined with the beauty of the surroundings, leaves
trekkers with a deep sense of satisfaction and accomplishment by the end of the
trek.</span></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;
color:#222222">&nbsp;</span></b></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><b><span style="font-size:12.0pt;
color:#222222">Himalayan / Mountain Flora and Fauna beauty and views </span></b></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;color:#222222">The
trek offers an opportunity to witness a wide variety of&nbsp;Himalayan <b>flora
and fauna forest and lakes river</b>, Himalayan tree from oak and pine forests
in the lower sections to vibrant meadows filled with wildflowers like high
altitude Himalayan Rhododendrons. The biodiversity adds to the richness of the
experience.</span></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;color:#222222">&nbsp;</span></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><b><u><span style="font-size:16.0pt;
color:#222222">Myth and the Name of the Rupin Pass Trek</span></u></b></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;color:#222222">Pronounced
"Rupin," the name Rupin is associated with a modern/legendary tale
about a beautiful village girl (Rupmati) who, according to legend, was
transformed into a river (Rupin) by divine intervention. These tales were told
to us by our grandparents; however, these stories are more popular among
trekkers/travel websites than religious or archival resources, as the saying
goes.</span></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;color:#222222">This
myth is not well documented historically; it is more typical of a local/travel
tale used to add cultural flavor.</span></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><b><u><span style="font-size:16.0pt;
color:#222222"><br /></span></u></b></p>






<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><b><u><span style="font-size:16.0pt;
color:#222222">Himalayan Hikers Start Work </span></u></b></p>








<p style="text-align:justify;line-height:
normal;background:white"><span style="font-size:12.0pt;color:#222222">How
it all began: Rupin Pass is now one of India's most popular high-altitude
trekking routes. The Himalayan Hikers team began offering trekking programs
around 1990. Mr. Bhagat Rawat and his team began their trekking journey here
when very few people knew about Rupin Pass. Bhagat Singh used to say,
"When groups arrived, we would be informed a month in advance or sent a
cash advance, saying, 'We are coming soon, and you should prepare for
us.'" Trekking wasn't easy at that time, and good equipment wasn't available
like today. The Himalayan Hikers team, a local trekking team, has been working
there ever since.1990</span></p>                     </div>
                     <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px;">
